&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Practice Manager &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Miller Street Surgery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Miller Street Surgery is looking to recruit an experienced pro-active Practice Nurse to join our existing team. We are a medium sized forward thinking practice with approximately 6,500 patients. The practice is situated in Newcastle under Lyme in Staffordshire and is a member of Newcastle Central Primary Care Network. The practice is made up of three partners and one salaried GP. We have an advanced nurse practitioner, one practice nurse and a healthcare assistant. We have team of admin support staff and a data quality co-ordinator and we also benefit from additional PCN clinical staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The suitable candidate will be a registered nurse with experience in working in General Practice. Existing experience in chronic disease management and elderly care is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder is responsible for ensuring the delivery of safe and effective general nursing care to the practice population. The candidate will work collaboratively with the whole general practice to provide routine nursing duties and in addition will work closely to support the practice partners and clinical team to achieve the indicators identified across all our clinical programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Only those applicants selected for interview will be contacted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Informal visits are encouraged and can be arranged on request.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: Dependent on experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact: Bernadette McCormick&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bernadette.mccormick@northstaffs.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
